text: @Zereul-MedikatedTurnip  "Bober" is a skewed pronounciation of Polish "bóbr", which means "beaver". That word is an example of several linguistic phenomena, that are characteristic to Polish language. Letter "ó" is pronounced exactly like "u", which in English is equal more to "oo", but you cannot use "ó" and "u" interchangeably, beacause "ó" often turns to "o" in some cases, exatly like here: "b[ó]br" - "b[o]ber". Second feature is a special "e", that comes between some consontants to ease some clusters, like here: "bób[]r" - "bob[e]r". As I always say, speaking Polish is kinda superpower - if you can speak that language... you will manage every other... 😆

Another great stream From our favorite shark. Great choice in games, I love kcd. Some tips if you want...




1. Pick all the flowers to level herbalism and get the perk "leg day" to level strength when picking flowers. It also is good for when you start doing alchemy to have so many ingredients saved up. Or just sell them for easy coin.

2. Train with captain Bernard as much as you can to level up your combat skills. 

3. Jumping and running will lvl up your vitality (every thing you do gives you xp in some way).

4. Talk to every one about every thing and Hagle for everything to level reputation and speech. 

5. When picking armor choos cafuly if you want to be a tank or stealthy.
